                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.922/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Siam</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Williams</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-18T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Referring to your despatches 181 November 17, and 191 November 26, 1921,
                    instructions based upon your 167, October 28, 1921, have been mailed to you. You
                    will avoid, save as the due protection of American interests may require, any
                    issue on this subject. For your confidential information. All provisions
                    concerning land tenure and many of the customary provisions for most favored
                    nation treatment were intentionally omitted from the Siamese Treaty in order to
                    avoid complicating certain pending questions such as that created by the alien
                    land laws recently adopted in various states.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
